pull_request.title: Ignore CFS0013 errors for non-Azure Artifact feeds
pull_request.body:
The main branch for the VMR is failing in internal builds for the `Secure Supply Chain Analysis` step with the error:

```
##[warning]src/format/tests/projects/for_analyzer_formatter/analyzer_project/NuGet.config - CFS0013: package source has value that is not an Azure Artifacts feed.
##[warning]src/nuget-client/test/EndToEnd/NuGet.Config - CFS0013: package source has value that is not an Azure Artifacts feed.
##[warning]src/nuget-client/test/NuGet.Tests.Apex/NuGet.OptProf/Assets/PackageReferenceSdk/nuget.config - CFS0013: package source has value that is not an Azure Artifacts feed.
##[warning]src/sdk/src/Tests/dotnet-new.Tests/Approvals/AllCommonItemsCreate.-o#NuGet-Config#-n#item.Linux.verified/NuGet-Config/nuget.config - CFS0013: package source has value that is not an Azure Artifacts feed.
##[warning]src/sdk/src/Tests/dotnet-new.Tests/Approvals/AllCommonItemsCreate.-o#NuGet-Config#-n#item.OSX.verified/NuGet-Config/nuget.config - CFS0013: package source has value that is not an Azure Artifacts feed.
##[warning]src/sdk/src/Tests/dotnet-new.Tests/Approvals/AllCommonItemsCreate.-o#NuGet-Config#-n#item.Windows.verified/NuGet-Config/nuget.config - CFS0013: package source has value that is not an Azure Artifacts feed.
##[warning]src/sdk/template_feed/Microsoft.DotNet.Common.ItemTemplates/content/Nuget/nuget.config - CFS0013: package source has value that is not an Azure Artifacts feed.
##[warning]src/source-build-externals/src/xunit/NuGet.Config - CFS0013: package source has value that is not an Azure Artifacts feed.

##[error]Azure Artifacts Configuration Analysis found 8 package configuration files in the repository which do not comply with Microsoft package feed security policies. The specific problems are listed above.
```

These same warnings show up in the release/8.0.1xx branch but do not produce an error for some reason. Perhaps it's because main is the default branch? The internal VMR pipeline is already configured with the variable: `cfsNugetWarnLevel=none`. But the error is happening anyway. The only way to get it to pass is by adding the .sscignore file to ignore CFS0013. The same is done in the sdk repo at https://github.com/dotnet/sdk/blob/main/.sscignore.
